00:00:23.200 --> 00:00:25.550
Raiders of the Lost Ark: Bringing a Gun to
a Sword Fight

00:00:25.550 --> 00:00:26.550
When Indiana Jones' leading lady is kidnapped
in search of a Holy relic in Raiders of the

00:00:26.550 --> 00:00:27.800
Lost Ark, Indy finds himself seriously outmatched.
Instead of trying to actually fight a skilled

00:00:27.800 --> 00:00:32.250
swordsman, Jones does the smart thing and
pulls out his gun and drops his opponent with

00:00:32.250 --> 00:00:37.170
a single shot. The original script had called
for a lengthy fight sequence, but when Harrison

00:00:37.170 --> 00:00:41.140
Ford was struck with food poisoning the night
before filming, his energy was so sapped on

00:00:41.140 --> 00:00:47.420
set that he asked Steven Spielberg if he could
simply shoot the man instead. The director

00:00:47.420 --> 00:00:51.649
agreed, and one of Indy's most iconic moments
was born.

00:00:51.649 --> 00:00:53.710
The Dark Knight: A Round of Applause

00:00:53.710 --> 00:00:58.000
Heath Ledger's Joker is a comic book villain
for the ages, blending anarchy with dark humor

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:02.610
in nearly every one of his scenes in Christopher
Nolan's The Dark Knight. After finding himself

00:01:02.610 --> 00:01:06.800
in police custody, he witnesses Jim Gordon's
promotion to the rank of Police Commissioner

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:12.250
firsthand. As the officers in the room applaud
their colleague, the mocking, expressionless

00:01:12.250 --> 00:01:16.070
clapping from the jail cell grabs all their
attention, putting the camera squarely on

00:01:16.070 --> 00:01:22.560
Joker � It�s a chilling moment that Ledger
completely improvised during the scene.

00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:25.390
Taxi Driver: You Talkin To Me?

00:01:25.390 --> 00:01:29.380
Martin Scorsese and Robert DeNiro will always
be remembered for the chilling tale of Travis

00:01:29.380 --> 00:01:34.590
Bickle, the insomniac star of Taxi Driver.
Bickle's unforgettable mirror monologue centered

00:01:34.590 --> 00:01:38.509
on a single question: "You talkin' to me?"
But the script only stated that Travis should

00:01:38.509 --> 00:01:42.570
begin speaking to himself in front of the
mirror, without any specific details on what

00:01:42.570 --> 00:01:50.220
sort of scene to play out. The lines which
followed were improvised by DeNiro entirely

00:01:50.220 --> 00:01:54.790
on the spot. His words, raised eyebrow, and
general attitude came to define the actor

00:01:54.790 --> 00:01:57.120
for decades to come.

00:01:57.120 --> 00:02:00.439
Aliens: Game Over, Man

00:02:00.439 --> 00:02:05.030
James Cameron's sequel to 'Alien' helped define
what sci-fi is today. Of the futuristic space

00:02:05.030 --> 00:02:09.590
marines now seen in film, TV, and even video
games, not every one of those soldiers has

00:02:09.590 --> 00:02:13.480
what it takes to bring down the franchise's
Xenomorph enemies. After the first attack

00:02:13.480 --> 00:02:17.340
decimates the marines and their drop ship
crash lands, the script called for Private

00:02:17.340 --> 00:02:21.950
Hudson to panic, but the actor decided to
add a bit of video game lingo to the line,

00:02:21.950 --> 00:02:24.980
giving the film one of its most beloved quotes.

00:02:24.980 --> 00:02:30.349
The Usual Suspects: The Line-up

00:02:30.349 --> 00:02:34.620
The most iconic scene from Bryan Singer's
'The Usual Suspects' centers on a police line-up

00:02:34.620 --> 00:02:38.910
of the film's main cast of criminals. But
writer Christopher McQuarrie came up with

00:02:38.910 --> 00:02:43.050
just a single line of dialogue for each actor
to repeat, meaning it was up to the actors

00:02:43.050 --> 00:02:50.810
to shape the rest of the scene. When it came
time to film, the actors tried to outdo one

00:02:50.810 --> 00:02:59.230
another, turning the scene into a mess of
laughter. Even McQuarrie himself got in on

00:02:59.230 --> 00:03:03.900
the action as the police officer on the intercom,
asking Benicio del Toro to offer the line

00:03:03.900 --> 00:03:09.040
"In English please," and getting an unscripted
response in return.

00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:12.959
