00:03:39.849 --> 00:03:45.300
film, it became one of the most famous lines
in movie history.

00:03:45.300 --> 00:03:47.319
The Empire Strikes Back: Han's Goodbye

00:03:47.319 --> 00:03:52.220
When the heroes of Star Wars find themselves
ambushed during the final act of The Empire

00:03:52.220 --> 00:03:56.810
Strike Back, Han Solo is captured by Boba
Fett. The bounty hunter plans to freeze Solo

00:03:56.810 --> 00:04:01.290
in carbonite and return to Jabba the Hutt.
With his character's future uncertain, Han

00:04:01.290 --> 00:04:05.030
and Leia were meant to say their goodbyes
in the form of matching "I Love you"s. But

00:04:05.030 --> 00:04:08.939
director Ivan Kershner felt something was
missing, and told Harrison Ford to respond

00:04:08.939 --> 00:04:18.989
the way he felt his character should before
shouting 'Action!' What Ford came up with

00:04:18.989 --> 00:04:23.240
captured the smuggler's attitude perfectly,
and offered a line no Star Wars fan will ever

00:04:23.240 --> 00:04:24.610
forget.

00:04:24.610 --> 00:04:28.580
The Shining: Here's Johnny!

00:04:28.580 --> 00:04:32.590
Stanley Kubrick's tale of supernatural and
psyhological terror was an instant classic.

00:04:32.590 --> 00:04:37.690
And its success was due as much to Jack Nicholson's
crazed descent into madness as it was to the

00:04:37.690 --> 00:04:41.970
novel The Shining is based on. When Jack turns
on his family he chases his wife and son into

00:04:41.970 --> 00:04:46.590
a bathroom and begins chopping through the
door with a fire axe. This is where he offers

00:04:46.590 --> 00:04:51.610
a twisted version of the phrase made famous
on The Tonight Show with Johnny Carson: "Heeeeeeere's

00:04:51.610 --> 00:04:57.000
Johnny!" The line became a shorthand for the
entire movie, even though it wasn�t in Kubrick's

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:02.009
original screenplay.
The Silence of the Lambs: A Nice Chianti

00:05:02.009 --> 00:05:06.410
Few cinematic psychopaths have even come close
to Anthony Hopkins� Hannibal Lecter in 'The

00:05:06.410 --> 00:05:09.950
Silence of The Lambs.' Hopkins was chilling
in every one of his scenes, but 'Hannibal

00:05:09.950 --> 00:05:15.460
the Cannibal' cemented his legacy with a single
anecdote involving a dinner of "fava beans,

00:05:15.460 --> 00:05:24.150
and a nice Chianti." Hannibal's specific tastes
were found in the script, but Hopkins' unsettling

00:05:24.150 --> 00:05:29.139
suckling sound effect wasn't. The actor had
started making the sound to creep out his

00:05:29.139 --> 00:05:34.200
co-star Jodie Foster during rehearsals, and
the director decided it was too good to leave

00:05:34.200 --> 00:05:35.200
out.

00:05:35.200 --> 00:05:36.889
Dumb &amp; Dumber: The Most Annoying Sound

00:05:36.889 --> 00:05:41.960
Jim Carrey and Jeff Daniels came up with tons
of unforgettable exchanges and physical gags

00:05:41.960 --> 00:05:45.789
as the co-leads of 'Dumb &amp; Dumber.' But in
a scene where a hitman discovers how the pair

00:05:45.789 --> 00:05:53.550
entertain themselves on long road trips, they
decided completely off script. The back and

00:05:53.550 --> 00:05:57.950
forth wordplay, poking, and Carrey's reveal
of 'the most annoying sound in the world'

00:05:57.950 --> 00:06:02.300
were all thought up on the spot with no warning
given to the actor between them. Check out

00:06:02.300 --> 00:06:04.750
that genuine reaction.

